"The user starts with View 1 at the [Overview] level to understand the overall distribution of demographic variables. By clicking on demographic categories, data filters are applied to subsequent views like Views 2 and 3. In View 2 at the [Exploration] level, the user explores the relationship between age and churn score using scatter plots and identifies specific patterns or anomalies. The user transitions to View 3, a heatmap at the [Exploration] level, for multi-dimensional analysis involving churn categories and age bins. Next, detailed correlations are examined in View 4, where the distribution of churn scores based on dependents is displayed with box plots, filtered through the selection made in View 2. Finally, insights are summarized in View 5, where the proportion of churned vs. non-churned customers is displayed using a stacked bar chart by gender and age bins."